By accessing or using this dataset (“Dataset”), you agree to the following terms:

1. Citation Requirement

If you publish work that uses this Dataset, you must include the following citation:

Olewave, “OleSpeech-IV: A Large-Scale Multispeaker and Multilingual Conversational Speech Dataset with Diverse Topics.” arXiv preprint, 2025.

If you provide a description in your work, you must use the following text. You may not mention any source names, brand names, podcast names, celebrity names, or other identifiers that reveal the original source and content of the Dataset.

“The audio content comes from publicly-available English podcasts and talk shows. Speaker names, turns, and transcripts are human-sourced and refined by a proprietary pipeline, while additional information such as timestamps and confidence scores is derived from the pipeline. Version 1.0 of the dataset is used.”

2. Acknowledgment

If you choose to acknowledge us, please use the following statement:

“We appreciate Olewave for providing the English conversational dataset.”

3. Non-Commercial Use Only

This Dataset may be used only for non-commercial research purposes. Commercial use of any kind is strictly prohibited without prior written permission from Olewave.

4. No Redistribution

You may not redistribute, sublicense, or share the Dataset in whole or in part. Access is granted solely for your individual research use.

5. Ownership and Control

All rights, title, and interest in the Dataset remain with Olewave. This Agreement grants only a limited, revocable license to use the Dataset under these terms.

6. Governing Law

This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of California, without regard to its conflict of laws principles.
